      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>While I agree with Frank Rich's opposition to the ''Religious Freedom Amendment'' (column, Jan. 7), a part of me hopes that it will pass just so that I can watch the horror of conservatives at the unintended consequences of their own actions.</p>
        <p>If we entrust our children's prayer lives to the education bureaucracy, they are sure to get the same quality education in religion that they have already received in science, history and other secular subjects. Also, politically correct bureaucrats will surely write multicultural prayers to deities from the world's polytheist traditions, and the children of Christian fundamentalists will be forced to say those prayers.</p>
        <p>DAVID J. EDMONDSON  Alexandria, Va., Jan. 7, 1998</p>
      </block>
